President Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of New York due to severe storms and flooding that occurred from July 9 to July 10, 2023. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Lai Sun Yee of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Damage assessments are ongoing, and more counties and forms of assistance may be designated in the future. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.